-- Chile Mine Accident Near Copiapo Leaves One Dead, 2 Trapped, Emol Reports
-- B y   R a n d a l l   W o o d s
-- 2010-11-08T18:40:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-08/chile-mine-accident-near-copiapo-leaves-one-dead-2-trapped-emol-reports.html
An accident at the Los Reyes mine
outside northern Chile’s city of Copiapo has left at least one
worker dead and two trapped, online news service Emol.com
reported.  A fourth miner is being treated for injuries, the Santiago-
based news service reported today, citing Carlos Garcia,
regional director of Chile’s national emergency office known as
Onemi.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Woods in Santiago at 
 rwoods13@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
